To compute the product of two matrices, we multiply the rows of the first matrix by the columns of the second matrix. 

Let $\mathbf{A} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 & 0 \\ 5 & -3 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\mathbf{B} = \begin{pmatrix} 8 & -2 \\ 1 & 1 \end{pmatrix}$. 

$\mathbf{AB} = \begin{pmatrix} (2)(8) + (0)(1) & (2)(-2) + (0)(1) \\ (5)(8) + (-3)(1) & (5)(-2) + (-3)(1) \end{pmatrix}$

$= \begin{pmatrix} 16 & -4 \\ 37 & -13 \end{pmatrix}$

Therefore, $\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 16 & -4 \\ 37 & -13 \end{pmatrix}}$ is the product of $\mathbf{A}$ and $\mathbf{B}$.
